25|$|The {{emergency}} physician, in German , {{must be a}} Physician with a Notfallmedizin (Emergency Medicine) board certification, {{issued by}} the State Chamber of Physicians. In order to obtain the board certification, a minimum term of residency in a specialty related to <b>critical</b> <b>care</b> <b>medicine,</b> additional training in techniques of anaesthetics and <b>critical</b> <b>care</b> <b>medicine</b> and the passing of a board examination is required. While the position is technically open to any physician who completes the board certification process, due to the inderdisciplinary nature of medical emergencies, most of the physicians employed as Notarzt are anaesthesiologists. The latter have mandatory service as a Notarzt during their specialty training.|$|E
