50|$|Intensive <b>Care</b> <b>Medicine</b> is {{a monthly}} peer {{reviewed}} medical journal covering intensive <b>care</b> or <b>critical</b> <b>care</b> and emergency <b>medicine.</b> It {{was established in}} 1975 as the European Journal of Intensive <b>Care</b> <b>Medicine</b> and obtained its current name in 1977. It is the official journal of the European Society of Intensive <b>Care</b> <b>Medicine</b> and the European Society of Paediatric and Neonatal Intensive Care. The editor-in-chief is Elie Azoulay (Paris Diderot University). It is published by Springer Science+Business Media.|$|R
